        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What Is OpenArt AI?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "OpenArt AI is a web-based platform for generating images, videos, and audio using artificial intelligence. It brings together over 100 premium models under one roof, including industry favorites like Stable Diffusion XL, FLUX, and advanced ControlNet workflows.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What makes it stand out is not just the model variety. It is the workspace. OpenArt gives you a clean, intuitive studio where you can experiment with prompts, fine-tune outputs, train personalized models, and even build consistent characters across multiple images. You do not need to install anything locally. Everything runs in your browser.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/what-is-openart-ai"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you want a deeper breakdown of the platform, check out ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "what OpenArt AI is and why it matters",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
