      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pro Tips for Better Results",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "After hundreds of generations, here are the patterns that consistently produce the best output:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Be specific with style keywords.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Instead of \"a painting,\" try \"oil painting with visible brushstrokes in the style of John Singer Sargent.\" Specificity is your friend.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use negative prompts.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " OpenArt supports negative prompts — tell the AI what you do NOT want (\"blurry, distorted hands, watermark\") and watch the quality jump.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Experiment with aspect ratios.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " A square crop feels different from a cinematic 21:9 ratio, even with the same prompt. Match your aspect ratio to the final use case.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Save your seeds.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " When you get a generation you love, note the seed number. You can then make small prompt tweaks while keeping the core composition identical.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Train a custom model.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " If you have a specific art style or character you work with regularly, investing 30 minutes in training a personalized model saves hours down the line.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Final Thoughts: Why OpenArt AI Earned a Permanent Spot in My Toolkit",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I cycle through AI tools constantly. Most get tested for a week and forgotten. OpenArt stayed. The reason is simple: it balances depth and accessibility better than almost anything else I have used. Beginners can generate beautiful images in minutes. Advanced users can dig into ControlNet, custom models, and workflow automation.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The new features — Seedance 2.0, consistent characters, audio generation — show that the team is not resting. They keep pushing the platform forward in ways that directly benefit creators.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you have been on the fence about AI image generation, or if you have tried other tools and felt underwhelmed, give OpenArt a real shot. The free tier lets you test everything without commitment.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
