      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The Advanced and Infinite plans include commercial use rights. This means you can use your generated images in products, marketing materials, client work, and other commercial applications. Always double-check the specific license terms for the models you use.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How does OpenArt AI compare to Midjourney or DALL-E?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "OpenArt stands out for its model variety — you get access to Stable Diffusion, FLUX, ControlNet, and 100+ other models in one place. Instead of being locked into a single AI architecture, you can choose the best tool for each project. The built-in editing suite, character consistency features, and video generation add layers of capability that many single-model platforms do not offer.",
